Former SAA board chair, Dudu Myeni has been implicated - again. It’s alleged she gave unlawful instructions to SAA subordinates. So claims the former SAA chief financial officer. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former SAA Chief Financial Officer Phumeza Nhantsi was scared to go against former chairperson Dudu Myeni. She told the Zondo commission she was often given unlawful instructions and told to appoint certain people. She says at some points she felt like her life was in danger. READ: State capture: Agrizzi implicates Dudu Myeni “The pressure she was putting was that she wanted us not to take things to the board and that was the board transaction.” Nhantsi concluded her testimony on Wednesday. The inquiry is dealing with allegations linked to SAA. The State Capture Inquiry has turned its focus to SA Express. Contracts at two North West airports are under scrutiny. Courtesy #DStv403